HEADWORD: Thoracostraca
<hw>Tho`ra*cos"tra*ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Thorax</er>, and <er>Ostracoid</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An extensive division of Crustacea, having a
dorsal shield or carapec<?/ <?/<?/niting all, or nearly all, of the
thoracic somites to the head. It includes the crabs, lobsters, shrimps,
and similar species.</def>⟦br⟧
